<body>
    <h1>Introduction to OpenAPI</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-WhatisOpenAPI?">What is OpenAPI?</h=
3>
<p><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manu=
al-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" heigh=
t=3D"125" src=3D"c960f915e931c9a4590439c03a5c336bb669fed9cd42c43074387115ec=
22b465" data-image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279302/OpenAPI-logo-sma=
ll.jpg?version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1718172110767&amp;api=3Dv2" data-=
unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1721953120" data-=
linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data=
-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"OpenAPI-logo-small.jpg" data-base-url=3D"=
https://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D=
"image/jpeg" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279302" data-linked-r=
esource-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span><span class=
=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img =
class=3D"confluence-embedded-image" draggable=3D"false" height=3D"175" src=
=3D"ce8bc9e2fd4b823d45124a7fb3c17061f5befbcac113f32eb9d09fa059dcf71b" data-=
image-src=3D"/download/attachments/1203279302/swagger-logo-horizontal.jpeg?=
version=3D1&amp;modificationDate=3D1663571074233&amp;api=3Dv2" data-unresol=
ved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resource-id=3D"1203279304" data-linked-=
resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource-type=3D"attachment" data-linked=
-resource-default-alias=3D"swagger-logo-horizontal.jpeg" data-base-url=3D"h=
ttps://confluence.srv.westpac.com.au" data-linked-resource-content-type=3D"=
image/jpeg" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"1203279302" data-linked-re=
source-container-version=3D"4" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></p>
<p>OpenAPI is a framework for describing your API using a common language t=
hat everyone can understand.</p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-WhatisanOpenAPISpecification?">What is an O=
penAPI Specification?</h3>
<p>An OpenAPI Specification is a set of rules for a format describing REST =
APIs. The specification defines the interface of the API describing all sup=
ported resources, operations and expected responses in a format that makes =
it easier to develop and consume an API. It is an easy-to-learn, language a=
gnostic, and both human and machine readable</p>
<p><strong>Further reading: </strong><a href=3D"https://swagger.io/docs/spe=
cification/about/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">https://swagger=
.io/docs/specification/about/</a></p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-BenefitsofOpenAPI">Benefits of OpenAPI</h3>
<ul>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>It's comprehensible for deve=
lopers and non-developers.</strong>&nbsp;Product managers, partners, and ev=
en potential clients can have input into the design of your API, because th=
ey can see it clearly mapped out in this friendly UI.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>It's human readable&nbsp;<em=
>and</em>&nbsp;machine readable.</strong>&nbsp;This means that not only can=
 this be shared with your team internally, but the same documentation can b=
e used to automate API-dependent processes.</span></li>
<li><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,0,0);"><strong>It's easily adjustable</stro=
ng>. This makes it great for testing and debugging API problems.</span></li=
>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-OpenAPI(SwaggerV3)Support">OpenAPI (Swagger=
 V3) Support</h3>
<p>The Mesh Platform initially only had support for Swagger v2. This suppor=
t has now been extended to OpenAPI (Swagger v3.0.3), and is the recommended=
 contract specification for new Mesh APIs.</p>
<p>Existing APIs with a swagger specification will continue to be supported=
 in the Mesh.</p>
<p>The Mesh Design guidelines apply to both OpenAPI and Swagger contracts.<=
/p>
<h3 id=3D"IntroductiontoOpenAPI-TheGoldenTemplate">The Golden Template</h3>
<p>The golden swagger specifications are the template that all Westpac Mesh=
 API specifications are to use when designing a Westpac Mesh API. <strong>Y=
ou must always go to the repository and get the latest golden swagger speci=
fications whenever you are&nbsp; extending an API.&nbsp;</strong>Newly crea=
ted APIs will already&nbsp;be initialised with a sample swagger specificati=
on based on the latest golden template.</p>
<p>Whenever you extend an API you must ensure that any changes you make are=
 backwards compatible. This includes any changes you make when incorporatin=
g changes in the latest golden specification.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<ul>
<li>Changes to the information block are backwards compatible</li>
<li>Adding a new mandatory header field is not backwards compatible</li>
</ul>
<p>If changes cannot be made in a backwards compatible fashion then discuss=
 this with your architect, as a new major version may be required. <strong>=
Further reading</strong> -&nbsp;<a href=3D"/display/MESH/API+Design+Standar=
ds#APIDesignStandards-versioning">API Design Standards#versioning</a></p>
<p>This repository contains the latest golden templates and some sample imp=
lementations. Please refer to the Readme.md for more information.</p>
<p><strong>Contract repository:</strong> <a class=3D"external-link" href=3D=
"https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/contracts/browse"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">https://bitbucket.srv.westpac.com.au/projects/WDP2/repos/=
contracts/browse</a></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
    </div>
</body>
